               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480612-name-200" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480612-name-200" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480612-name-200" type="surname" value="WOOD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480612-name-200" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES WOOD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a woollen-draper in Bishopsgate-street. On 6th Juno I was at my door, talking to Mr. May—I heard that a piece of cloth Had been taken—I went out with May, and saw a person running, but</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184806120018"></xptr>
               <p>having no one in my shop I returned—I afterwards saw this cloth at the station—it is mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480612-name-201" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480612-name-201" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480612-name-201" type="surname" value="MAY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480612-name-201" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES MAY</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Cornhill. I was talking to Mr. Wood—we received information—I ran to Bishopsgate Church, and up Cutler-street, and saw the prisoner with this cloth—I asked where he got it—he said he bought it—I took him and the cloth—this is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480612-name-202" type="witnessName">
